AB  - It has been widely accepted that asymmetric information is one of the key issues in financing informationally opaque small and entrepreneurial businesses. It is central to understanding the lending decision of financiers, such as banks and venture capitalists, and corporate decisions of businesses, in terms of financing, investment and performance. This chapter aims to provide a review of the importance of information asymmetries in entrepreneurial finance from three aspects. First, it reviews existing theoretical frameworks for information asymmetries and entrepreneurial finance. Second, it summarises a variety of empirical measurements of information asymmetries and the roles they play in entrepreneurial finance. Finally, the chapter offers empirical evidence of the roles played by information asymmetries concerning access to finance, investment, and working capital management of small and entrepreneurial businesses.
